  "texts": [
    "Biosynthetic pathways for the production of 3,4dihydroxybenzoate and tyramine have already been engineered into S. cerevisiae 45, 46, with high-throughput screening methods yielding improved tyrosine precursor yields 47.",
    "Second, the early pathway enzymes for the production of norbelladine, norcraugsodine reductase, and norbelladine synthase must be functionally expressed in a microbial strain.",
    "So far, the activities of these enzymes have only been demonstrated within an in vitro context [48] [49] [50].",
    "Third, the downstream enzymes necessary for the production of advanced AAs must be identified and functionally expressed.",
    "With regards to galantamine, the CYP96T1 and CYP96T6 cytochrome proteins have been shown to catalyze the para-ortho coupling of 4NB and thus produce the galantamine precursor N-demethylnarwedine 51, 52."
  ],
